<div class="col two-sm last" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn2">
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Travel information</h3>
<p>Rotherham Hospital is situated on Moorgate Road approximately 1.5 miles away from the town centre and is on many bus routes, with bus stops in the Hospital Grounds as well as outside the 2 main entrances.</p><br/><p>If you are coming from Rotherham town centre, the Rotherham Hospital site is 1 mile from the Town Hall heading towards Whiston Crossroads.</p><br/><p>If you are coming from Maltby, Bramley and Wickersley, take the A631 (Bawtry Road) to Whiston Crossroads and turn right onto Moorgate Road, the hospital is 1/2mile along Moorgate on the left hand side.</p><br/><p>More directions and maps can be found on our website.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Parking</h3>
<p>There are car parks near each main entrance to the hospital. The car parks can get full quickly, so if you are visiting the hospital for an appointment please allow extra time for parking. <br/>Car parking is currently free of charge</p>
